"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-05-aussie-olympians-slam-farcical-egg-spoon-event-paris-2024-21362287\", \"text\": \"The mixed 4\\u00d7100m medley relay has been labelled 'farcical' and 'the egg-and-spoon race of theOlympic Games' by a former Australian Olympian, despite the country claiming bronze in the event.  The mixed event came into the Games for the first time in Tokyo, becoming the first ever mixed-gender swimming contest at the Olympics.  Team GB won the gold inJapan, with USA claiming first prize in Paris, ahead ofChinain silver and the Aussies in bronze place.  However, three-time Olympic medallist forAustraliaJames Magnussen is no fan of the event, questioning whether it should be in the Games at all.  Follow\\u00a0Metro.co.uk's live blog for updates from the Paris 2024 Olympics.  'I would call it the egg-and-spoon race of theOlympic Games. It is farcical,' Magnussen said on the Matty and the Missile inParispodcast. 'We have got men swimming against women. Kaylee McKeown won the gold medal in the 100m backstroke, she goes up againstRyan Murphy, who got bronze in the men's 100m backstroke. There is about a 15m difference.  'On their own, they are both amazing products \\u2026 I do not know why we'd want to compare male athletes and female athletes. And then the race itself just ends up this absolute jungle, where one person's ten metres ahead, then the other team switches. You have got male breaststrokers vs female breaststrokers.  'It's just a shambles of an event. I can not understand why it's at the Olympic Games, and I can not understand giving out Olympic medals to that event.  'You are telling me at the end of the day that that's worth the same as individual gold for Ariarne Titmus in the 400m freestyle? It's not comparable.'  Aussie legend Stephanie Rice won three golds in the pool at Beijing 2008 and she too has doubts about the mixed event.  'I feel very mixed about it. I feel like it's a token event. In the sense that it feels more fun, than a purist race,' she said on Stan Sports' Olympic Daily.  'But I like that swimming is looking at different ways of evolving. That's the same as the men having an 800 metre freestyle and the women having a 1500 metre freestyle.'  For more stories like this,check our sport page.  Follow Metro Sport for the latest news onFacebook,TwitterandInstagram.  ArrowMORE:Avoid these easily misunderstood phrases while travelling in France  ArrowMORE:Team GB athlete in 'floods of tears' after terrible Olympic pole vault attempt  ArrowMORE:What does repechage mean at the Paris 2024 Olympics? How it works  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.  Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply. Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.  Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply. Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy\"}"